<HEAD>Armed Man Holds Family Hostage</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SPRINGFIELD, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 An armed man who police say had been hospitalized recently for depression was holding his girlfriend, her sister and the girlfriend's 4-year-old daughter hostage late Saturday. Heavily armed police remained in position around a one-story home where <PERSON> Douglas </PERSON> `` Dougie'' <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON>, 20, was holding the three hostages. A fourth hostage, the 2 -LCB- - month-old daughter of <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON> and his girlfriend, was released in the morning, pushed out of the house wrapped in a quilt, police said Police blocked off streets leading to the house and evacuated about 32 families about five hours after receiving the first reports of the disturbance late Friday. <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON> was reportedly armed with a handgun and threatened to kill himself and the hostages. Twice during the day he fired shots inside the house, but he allowed the hostages to talk to police each time to show they had not been harmed, police said. `` We're just going to wait,'' said Police Chief <PERSON> Mike </PERSON> <PERSON> Walton </PERSON>. `` Right now, everything is under control.'' Police spokesman <PERSON> Neil </PERSON> <PERSON> Williamson </PERSON> said <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON> had made no specific demands but he repeatedly asked to talk to friends and relatives by telephone. `` He seems like he's almost hallucinating,'' said police spokesman <PERSON> Neil </PERSON> <PERSON> Williamson </PERSON>. He said <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON> was hospitalized recently for depression and apparently had been taking medication that might affect his mood. <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> Kerr </PERSON>, a friend who talked to Thomas by telephone during the afternoon, described him as `` paranoid and insecure.'' Although <PERSON> Williamson </PERSON> refused to identify him, relatives, friends and other police sources confirmed <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON>' identity, according to the <ORGANIZATION> Springfield </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> State </ORGANIZATION> <ORGA