<DATELINE>SAN SALVADOR, El Salvador (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Security forces shot to death a news photographer and wounded his colleague at a checkpoint near <LOCATION> Ilopango </LOCATION> Air Force Base on the eve of <LOCATION> El </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Salvador </LOCATION>'s presidential election, officials said Sunday. Both men were Salvadoran free-lance photographers who worked regularly for the <ORGANIZATION> Reuters </ORGANIZATION> news agency. Representatives of the agency in <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Salvador </LOCATION> declined to comment. Armed Forces officials were not immediately available for comment. Justice of the Peace <PERSON> Manuel </PERSON> <PERSON> Jesus </PERSON> <PERSON> de </PERSON> <PERSON> Aguilar </PERSON> said troops who brought in the body of <PERSON> Roberto </PERSON> <PERSON> Navas </PERSON>, 28, said the shooting occurred when the two men's motorcycle failed to stop at an air force checkpoint late Saturday night. The magistrate said soldiers radioed the next checkpoint and that troops there shot the two men when they again refused to stop. The armed forces have been on full alert since Tuesday when leftist guerrillas stepped up their campaign to disrupt Sunday's election <PERSON> Navas </PERSON> was shot twice, in the back and the side. The judge said he found at least 22 spent rounds at the scene. <PERSON> Luis </PERSON> <PERSON> Galdamez </PERSON>, 34, was shot once in the back and underwent emergency surgery at <LOCATION> Hospital </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Rosales </LOCATION> in <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Salvador </LOCATION>. Dr. <PERSON> Marcelino </PERSON> <PERSON> Caballero </PERSON> told <ORGANIZATION> The </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> the bullet entered <PERSON> Galdamez </PERSON>'s back and exited through his upper right arm, injuring a lung. The doctor described the injuries as serious. Colleagues said <PERSON> Navas </PERSON> lived near the base, one of the most strategic military installations i