at a discount $ 49 a ride _ because it attracted many of the business people who most frequently use the shuttle. The weekday rates return to their normal $ 99 this week. <ORGANIZATION> Mattell </ORGANIZATION> added that <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION>'s Latin American routes are seeing steadily increasing loads. He declined to comment on a threat Saturday by <ORGANIZATION> Teamsters </ORGANIZATION> union leader <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> F. </PERSON> <PERSON> Genoese </PERSON> to organize a sympathy walkout at <ORGANIZATION> Pan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> World </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airways </ORGANIZATION> concentrating on the Pan Am Northeast shuttle. <ORGANIZATION> Pan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Am </ORGANIZATION> spokeswoman <PERSON> Pamela </PERSON> <PERSON> Hanlon </PERSON> said the company, which has boosted its Northeast shuttle service during the strike, does n't expect a Teamsters walkout `` We believe our employees are n't inclined to take any kind of job action,'' she said Genoese met in <LOCATION> Miami </LOCATION> over the weekend with <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Machinists </ORGANIZATION> leader <PERSON> Charles </PERSON> <PERSON> E. </PERSON> <PERSON> Bryan </PERSON> to discuss strategy, including a joint employee buyout effort to combine Eastern with <ORGANIZATION> Pan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Am </ORGANIZATION>. They said that <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Pan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Am </ORGANIZATION> routes would complement each other and that joining the carriers would be a way to save both. Both have been beset by labor problems and have lost a total of $ 2 billion in the 1980s. Besides the advertisement for pilots, <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> took out full-page ads in leading <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Coast </LOCATION> newspapers calling itself a fighting underdog determined to come